OL,3,CD-Day veteran reflects on 'dreadful
OL,4,Csights' at Normandy landings
OL,6,F80 years on from D-Day, there are
OL,7,Fbelieved to be only around a hundred
OL,8,Fsurviving British veterans of
OL,9,FOperation Overlord.
OL,11,FOne of those is 103-year-old John
OL,12,FMcOwan from Peebles.
OL,14,FAfter serving with the Royal
OL,15,FElectrical and Mechanical Engineers in
OL,16,Fthe 7th Armoured Division in North
OL,17,FAfrica and Italy he landed on Gold
OL,18,FBeach in Normandy as part of the
OL,19,FAllied effort to liberate Nazi-
OL,20,Foccupied Europe.
