OL,3,CD-Day veteran reflects on 'dreadful
OL,4,Csights' at Normandy landings
OL,6,FAs Sgt. McOwan progressed through
OL,7,Fnorthern France, he saw first-hand the
OL,8,Fdevastation left in the so-called
OL,9,FFalaise Pocket which became known as
OL,10,FThe Corridor of Death.
OL,12,F"It was a dreadful sight because the
OL,13,FRAF had been able to bomb them, just
OL,14,Fas though they were almost like
OL,15,Fsitting ducks
OL,17,F"Everywhere was burnt-out vehicles and
OL,18,Ftanks.
OL,20,F"There were so many dead bodies, you
OL,21,Fcould almost walk over them.
